^ - ------------------ new and emerging occupations -------------------- 
^ audiologists 
^ thanks to medical advances , people are now enjoying longer lives than ever before . 
^ and as the elderly population in the &name &name grows larger , so does the demand for care services that center around the elderly . 
^ &char perfect example : audiologists . 
^ audiologists specialize in evaluating , treating and researching hearing problems . 
^ they try to figure out exactly what kind of hearing loss is occurring and help find treatments . 
^ audiologists may work &num with patients ( such as fitting a client with a hearing aid ) or they may work for a company , measuring noise levels in workplaces . 
^ audiologists may also work with children , testing their listening skills and trying to catch any hearing loss before it becomes too serious . 
^ and since the federal law now promises special education classes for children with disabilities , the need for audiologists in public schools is growing quickly . 
^ to launch a career as an audiologist , you 'll need a master 's degree in audiology . 
^ you may also need a certificate of clinical competence . 
